value.title: Biden deputy chief of staff touted 'mandatory buybacks' of assault weapons

value.title: Biden acknowledges 'real brick walls' he'll face in Senate during video call with supporters
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden acknowledged in a private video call with supporters on Wednesday that he will face "real brick walls" in the Senate if Republicans maintain their majority but said he thinks he can overcome the political divides that may exist.

value.title: Angry at election defeat, Trump seeks partial recount in Wisconsin
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's re-election campaign said on Wednesday it was seeking a partial recount of Wisconsin's presidential election results, as part of its long-shot attempt to reverse President-elect Joe Biden's victory.

value.title: Sen. Kennedy blasts Cuomo complaints about Trump 'ego', compares it to 'being called ugly by a frog'
value.excerpt: Democratic New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo is the last person with any standing to complain about President Trump's "ego," Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., told "Bill Hemmer Reports" Wednesday.

value.title: NYC subway system faces steep cuts; MTA chairman calls on 'Amtrak Joe' Biden to stave off 9,400 layoffs
value.excerpt: New York City subways and buses could lose nearly 7,000 jobs amid service reductions of up to 40%. Commuter rail fare increases are also possible.

value.title: Kevin McCarthy, the House Minority Leader, Doesn’t Think Trump Is Going Away
value.excerpt: The California Republican believes his party’s victories in 2020 came thanks to the president, not in spite of him: “He brought turnout.”

value.title: Candace Owens: Newsom will follow 'Marxist' BLM, appoint Black woman to replace Kamala Harris in Senate
value.excerpt: California Gov. Gavin Newsom will bend the knee to Black Lives Matter, author Candace Owens argued on Wednesday, reacting to the organization calling on Newsom to appoint a Black woman to fill the senate seat vacated by Kamala Harris.

value.title: Election 2020 live updates: Half of Republicans say Trump 'rightfully won' election, poll finds

value.excerpt: Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif., is wrong about President Trump's tweets inciting violence, Sen. Mike Lee, R-Utah, said Wednesday.

value.title: Jones, Yates, Becerra among names floated for Biden attorney general
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is considering several individuals to serve as the attorney general in his administration, including former Alabama Sen. Doug Jones, former Deputy Attorney General Sally Yates and California Attorney General Xavier Becerra, Fox News is told.

value.title: Republican election chief says Trump would've won Georgia by 10,000 votes if he hadn't 'suppressed his own voting base'

value.excerpt: The president's refusal to acknowledge defeat isn't the first time Georgia voters have heard that, but state officials say claims about impropriety — past and present — are false.

value.title: Trump lashes out in new bid to tarnish an election he lost
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump flexed the power of his office Tuesday to tarnish America's free and fair election, sacking the official who declared the vote the most secure in US history, even as more of his false claims of massive fraud were exposed as baseless in court.

value.title: Trump fires top U.S. election cybersecurity official who defended vote
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Tuesday fired top cybersecurity official Chris Krebs in a message on Twitter, accusing him without evidence of making a "highly inaccurate" statement affirming the Nov. 3 election was secure and rejecting claims of fraud.

value.title: The Point: Lindsey Graham just crossed another line in defending Trump
value.excerpt: Fresh off a surprisingly pedestrian election win on November 3, Lindsey Graham has decided to take on a new role: The most aggressive enforcer of the idea that President Donald Trump maybe -- just maybe! -- didn't lose the 2020 election.
